The conservative party “does not object” to the new abbreviation, but notes that MWP is close to the word Muppet.
In this context, the letter w in the Welsh language is spoken roughly as the letter u in the Yorkshire dialect of English.
The Assembly Committee, currently drafting the change of name bill, made the following statement: “The final decision on the name of the members of the Assembly will of course remain with them”.
The Welsh Governance Act 2017 empowers the National Assembly of Wales to change its name.
In June, the Committee published a public opinion poll on the proposed options, according to which the Welsh Parliament instead of the Assembly had found widespread support among the local population.
With regard to the name of the members of the Assembly, the Committee preferred the Welsh Parliament Members option, while the MWP option received the greatest public support.
