2004: A severe earthquake on the western coast of the Indonesian province of Aceh in northern Sumatra on 26 December caused a tsunami that struck 14 countries, killing 226,000 people along the coast of the Indian Ocean, more than half of them in Aceh.
2005: A sequence of severe earthquakes struck the western coast of Sumatra in late March and early April.
