2010: An earthquake of 7.5 occurred on one of the Mentawai Islands at Sumatra, causing a tsunami of up to 10 metres, which destroyed dozens of villages and killed some 300 people.
2016: A weak earthquake struck Pidi Jaya district in Aceh, causing destruction and panic, as people remembered the devastating earthquake of 2004 and the tsunami.
