According to FWC, in the districts of Pinellas, Manati, Sarasota, Charlotte, and Collier, there are reports of large blooms, indicating a decrease in the concentration of microorganisms.
The Red Tide extends approximately 130 miles of the coastline from the northern Pinell to the southern districts of Lee.
